Option Screener
	- The purpose of the option screener is to look for Call options that require very little upward movement in the underlying security in order to turn a profit


Usage:
	screener [<options>] --expiration-date <YYYY-MM-DD>

		[--file <ticker symbol file>] 	a file containing ticker symbols, one per line
		[--symbol <ticker symbol>]  	a ticket symbol to evaulate
		[--yield-threshold <value%>] 	minimum dividend yield percentage
		[--max-call-cost <value>] 		maximum ask price for the call option
		[--max-break-even <value%>] 	maximum percentage gain to break even
		[--max-pe-ratio <value>] 		maximum P/E ratio
		--expiration-date <YYYY-MM-DD>	options expiration date
